# PowerShell User Guide for Windows

## Introduction

PowerShell is a powerful scripting language and command-line shell designed for system administration and automation. This
guide provides an overview of how to use PowerShell on Windows platforms.

## Getting Started

To get started with PowerShell on Windows, follow these steps:

- Using the `menu.ps1` script to interactively select and install development tools
- Running PowerShell scripts to automate tasks

## files ypu will find in the powershell folder
You can run the following scripts located in the `Platforms/windows/powershell/` directory:

cd Platforms/windows/powershell/

Test using Vm if you dont Trust the scripts/edit them before running.

```powershell

./menu.ps1
./setup.ps1
./env.ps1

```
- `menu.ps1` , `setup.ps1`, `env.ps1`: These scripts help in setting up the development environment and installing necessary tools.

## Features 
- Interactive menu for selecting and installing development tools
- Automated downloading of development tools
- Environment setup for development


